doc_summary_long: Poland is given two weeks to end its destruction of the Unesco-protected forest in a landmark ruling by the European court of justice. Poland has been given two weeks to stop illegal deforestation in the Unesco-protected Białowieża forest or face fines of at least €100,000 a day. In a precedent-setting ruling that will echo across the EU, the European court of justice ordered Poland to show it was acting lawfully in the ancient woodland, or face a €36.5m (£32m) annual penalty.
doc_summary_short: Poland is given two weeks to end its destruction of the Unesco-protected forest in a landmark ruling by the European court of justice.
doc_title: Poland faces €100,000-a-day fines over illegal logging in Białowieża forest
